\section{Analytic treatment of a self-gravitating radiation in a spherical shell around a strong fake horizon}
	\label{sec:4}

A strong {\it fake horizon}, which is a {\it fake horizon} with $\nu \sim 0$, is an especially interesting object because it is on the verge of becoming a true event horizon in the sense that $m(r_{\rm fh}) \approx r_{\rm fh}/2$. 

We hope that this interesting case allows an analytic description, which turns out to be true.

